<div id="Item_0" class="PageTitle"><div class="Options"></div><h1>Promotion and Badge (Spenser R. Welker)</h1></div>

<div id="Discussion_17386" class="Item ItemDiscussion">
    <div class="Discussion">
        <div class="Item-Header DiscussionHeader">
            <div class="AuthorWrap">
            <span class="Author">
                <a title="T4 Ceglar [Ret.]" href="https://vanilla.29th.org/profile/T4%20Ceglar%20%5BRet.%5D" class="PhotoWrap"><img src="../../uploads/defaultavatar/n154KLUS2L8EB.jpg" alt="T4 Ceglar [Ret.]" class="ProfilePhoto ProfilePhotoMedium" /></a><a href="https://vanilla.29th.org/profile/T4%20Ceglar%20%5BRet.%5D" class="Username">T4 Ceglar [Ret.]</a>            </span>
            <span class="AuthorInfo">
                            </span>
            </div>
            <div class="Meta DiscussionMeta">
            <span class="MItem DateCreated">
                <a href="promotion-and-badge-spenser-r-welker" class="Permalink" rel="nofollow"><time title="March 22, 2017 10:07PM" datetime="2017-03-22T22:07:28+00:00">March 2017</time></a>            </span>
                <span class="MItem"> <span title="Edited March 22, 2017 10:08PM by T4 Ceglar [Ret.]." class="DateUpdated">edited March 2017</span> </span>                 <span class="MItem Category"> in <a href="../../categories/promotions-and-awards">Promotions and Awards</a></span>             </div>
        </div>
                <div class="Item-BodyWrap">
            <div class="Item-Body">
                <div class="Message userContent">
                    <p>Cpl. Sommer said:</p>

<blockquote class="UserQuote"><div class="QuoteText">
  <p>Pvt. Welker has been a great addition to the squad. Since joining S1 from Able Company a couple months back, Pvt. Welker has quickly sharpened his skills on the battlefield. In addition to being a killing machine, he is not afraid to call out targets for the rest of the squad. Because of all the aforementioned abilities Pvt. Welker has showed, We see no other way than a promotion to PFC and awarding him the Rifle Marksman Badge.</p>
</div></blockquote>

<hr />

<p></p><div style="text-align: center;">

<p><img src="http://personnel.29th.org/images/forums/29thsealheaderblack.png" alt="" title="" /></p>

<p>CERTIFICATION OF PROMOTION</p>

<p><b>TO ALL WHO SHALL SEE THESE PRESENTS, GREETING:</b></p>

<p><span style="font-size: medium;">Know Ye, that reposing special trust and<br /> confidence in the fidelity and abilities of</span></p>

<p><code><a rel="nofollow" href="http://personnel.29th.org/#members/2296">Spenser R. Welker</a> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 979525370 &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; BP2S1</code></p>

<p><span style="font-size: medium;">I do promote him to <u>Private, First Class</u> in the </span></p>

<p><span style="font-size: xx-large;">UNITED STATES ARMY</span></p>

<p>to rank as such from the <u> 22nd </u> day of <u> March 2017 </u>.</p>

<p>You are charged to discharge carefully and diligently the duties of the grade to which promoted and to uphold the traditions and standards of the Army.</p>

<p>Effective with this promotion you are charged to execute diligently your special skills with a high degree of technical proficiency and to maintain standards of performance, moral courage and dedication to the Army which will serve as outstanding examples to your fellow soldiers. You are charged to observe and follow the orders and directions given by superiors acting according to the law, articles and rules governing the discipline of the Army. Your unfailing trust in superiors and loyalty to your peers will significantly contribute to the readiness and honor of the United States Army.</p>

<p><img src="http://personnel.29th.org/images/forums/29thsealfooter.png" alt="" /></p>

<p></p></div>

<p><img src="http://personnel.29th.org/images/forums/LTC_Wheatley.png" alt="" /></p>

<p><br /></p>

<p><br /></p>

<p><br /></p>

<hr />

<p></p><div style="text-align: center;"><img src="http://personnel.29th.org/images/badges/marksman/rifle.gif" alt="" title="Rifle Marksman Badge" /></div>
                </div>
